## Project Description

You are developing **RYLA** - an AI Influencer platform that enables users to create, customize, and generate content with AI-powered virtual influencers.

Supported platforms:

- Web app (Next.js)
- Landing page (Next.js)
- Payment funnel (Next.js)
- Backend API (NestJS)
- Admin dashboard (Next.js)

## Project Technologies Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 14 (App Router)
- **Frontend**: React 18, TypeScript 5.9
- **Backend**: NestJS 11, Node.js
- **Monorepo**: Nx 22
- **State Management**: Zustand 5
- **Database**: PostgreSQL with Drizzle ORM
- **Auth**: Supabase Auth
- **Storage**: Cloudflare R2 (S3-compatible)
- **Payments**: Finby
- **Analytics**: PostHog
- **Testing**: Vitest, Playwright
- **UI Components**: Radix UI, Tailwind CSS
- **Forms**: React Hook Form
- **Data Fetching**: TanStack Query (React Query)
- **API**: tRPC 11
- **Icons**: Lucide React
- **Animations**: Framer Motion
- **Email**: React Email, Resend

## Project Structure

```
apps/
  web/       # Main web app (app.ryla.ai)
  api/       # Backend API (end.ryla.ai)
  funnel/    # Payment funnel (goviral.ryla.ai)
  landing/   # Landing page (ryla.ai)
  admin/     # Admin dashboard
libs/
  shared/    # @ryla/shared - Utils, types, constants
  business/  # @ryla/business - Services, models, rules
  data/      # @ryla/data - Repositories, Drizzle schemas
  ui/        # @ryla/ui - Shared React components
  analytics/ # @ryla/analytics - Event tracking
  trpc/      # @ryla/trpc - tRPC routers
  payments/  # @ryla/payments - Payment integration
```

## Key Principles

- **MVP Focus**: Build fast, validate early, iterate on data
- **Layered Architecture**: Apps → Business → Data → DB
- **10-Phase Pipeline**: Strict development workflow
- **Type Safety**: Strict TypeScript, no `any`
- **Testing**: Business logic first, integration tests for critical paths
